## Building a Transfer List in React

**Mental model:** Two lists (left/right) plus a *selection* set of items the user has ticked. Move buttons shift selected items between sides. Model the two columns as arrays and the ticks as a `Set`; moving is array filter + concat, then clear the moved ticks.

### Step 1 — Two arrays + a checked Set
```jsx
const [left, setLeft] = useState(initialLeft);
const [right, setRight] = useState(initialRight);
const [checked, setChecked] = useState(new Set());
```

### Step 2 — Toggle a tick
```jsx
const toggle = (id) => setChecked((s) => {
  const n = new Set(s); n.has(id) ? n.delete(id) : n.add(id); return n;
});
```

### Step 3 — Move checked across
Partition the source by checked-ness; append to the target.

```jsx
const moveRight = () => {
  const moving = left.filter((i) => checked.has(i.id));
  setRight((r) => [...r, ...moving]);
  setLeft((l) => l.filter((i) => !checked.has(i.id)));
  setChecked(new Set());
};
```

### Step 4 — Enable buttons by selection side
```jsx
<button disabled={!left.some((i) => checked.has(i.id))} onClick={moveRight}>›</button>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Tick then move other side | Clear `checked` after each move. |
| Move all | Buttons that ignore selection and move everything. |
| Duplicate ids | Ids must be unique across both lists. |

**Interview tip:** Keeping a single `checked` Set that spans both columns (and clearing it after a move) is cleaner than per-list selection state — call out that the move is just filter-out-of-source + concat-into-target.

