## Building a Transfer List in Vue 3

**Mental model:** Two lists (left/right) plus a `Set` of ticked item ids spanning both. Move buttons shift ticked items across; moving is filter-out-of-source + push-into-target, then clear the ticks. `computed` flags drive button enablement.

### Step 1 — Two arrays + checked Set
```vue
<script setup>
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';
const left = ref(initialLeft);
const right = ref(initialRight);
const checked = ref(new Set());
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Toggle a tick
```js
function toggle(id) {
  const n = new Set(checked.value);
  n.has(id) ? n.delete(id) : n.add(id);
  checked.value = n;
}
```

### Step 3 — Move checked across
```js
function moveRight() {
  const moving = left.value.filter((i) => checked.value.has(i.id));
  right.value = [...right.value, ...moving];
  left.value = left.value.filter((i) => !checked.value.has(i.id));
  checked.value = new Set();
}
```

### Step 4 — Enable buttons by side
```js
const leftChecked = computed(() => left.value.some((i) => checked.value.has(i.id)));
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Mixed ticks | Clear `checked` after each move. |
| Empty side | Show an "(empty)" row. |
| Unique ids | Required across both lists. |

**Interview tip:** A single shared `checked` Set plus `computed` enablement flags keeps the logic DRY — the move itself is just two array operations and a reset.

